<table>
<tr><td>Acanthocereus tetragonus originated from Central America. 'Fairy Castle' is a
"miniature" cultivar (it can still reach 2&nbsp;m height) with many curved branches. Sadly,
the chlorophyl of two of these has died leaving them colourless; plants were
firm and roots looking good until the end.
