<tr><td>Hatiora rosea from Brazil, known as the Easter Cactus from its blooming time, is an
epiphyte in its natural habitat. When grown in soil, the roots need access to air or it rots.
It needs a cool (but non-freezing) winter to bloom, cooler than most North American homes.
