<tr><td>Senecio pendulus is a succulent native to mountains of north-east Africa, often called
"inchworm" from its growth habit. Its classification has bounced around among several genera.
<td width=10><td width=75>
<span class="thumbnail"><img src="images/s82.jpg" width=75 height=75 border=0 alt=""><span>
